    "description": "<p>Psions are masters of telekinesis and telepathy whose minds have ascended to be able to reach out to the world and&nbsp;creatures around them with their thoughts alone. They can both use telekinesis to move creatures and objects, and telepathy to assault creatures' minds.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Source of Power</em>:</strong> Psions have achieved a mental state of being where they can turn their own thoughts into reality as well as reach out to the minds of others. Psions have a wide range of origin, ranging from being born with a mental connection to the world around them, a strange psychic interaction, or years of training and mental strain.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Starting Equipment</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>1 Light Weapon</li>\n<li>1 set of Novice Light Armor</li>\n<li>X or Y &ldquo;Packs&rdquo; (Adventuring Packs Coming Soon)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Psion Spellcasting Mastery</h2>\n<p><strong>Combat Masteries:</strong> Light Weapons, Light Armor,&nbsp;Spellcasting.</p>\n<p><strong>Spell List:</strong> When you learn a new Spell, you can choose any&nbsp;Spell from any Spell List, but only Spells with Psychic or&nbsp;Gravity Spell Tags, or from the following Schools of Magic:&nbsp;Abjuration, Divination, Enchantment, or Illusion.</p>\n<p><strong>Alpha Note: </strong>You get access to the &ldquo;Premade List&rdquo; of&nbsp;Psychic &amp; Enchantment. This is the only Premade List&nbsp;that you have to choose from until the Spell List Alpha&nbsp;Update. Keep in mind that you do not get ALL of the&nbsp;Spells on this list, since the Psion only has 2 Cantrips and&nbsp;3 Spells at Level 1.</p>\n<p><strong>Cantrips Known:</strong> You learn a number of Spells with the&nbsp;Cantrip Spell Tag as shown in the Cantrips Known column of&nbsp;the Psion Class Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Spells Known:&nbsp;</strong>You learn an additional number of Spells&nbsp;(with or without the Cantrip Spell Tag) as shown in the Spells&nbsp;Known column of the Psion Class Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Mana Points:&nbsp;</strong>You have a maximum number of Mana Points&nbsp;equal to your Charisma or Intelligence, whichever is higher.&nbsp;Additionally, your maximum increases by an amount as&nbsp;shown in the Mana Points column of the Psion Class Table</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Class Table</h2>\n<table style=\"border-width: 2px; border-style: solid;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Level</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Bonus HP</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Attribute Points</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Skill Points</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>&nbsp;Mana&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Cantrips Known</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: rgb(132, 153, 189);\"><strong>Spells Known</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Features</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px;\"><strong>1</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px;\">2 (start)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px;\">5 (start)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px;\">Class Features</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-wid